00:01:41.245 --> 00:01:45.056
- [Ajit] Among the oldest
questions of humans are:

00:01:45.056 --> 00:01:48.729
Who are we? What are we doing here?

00:01:48.729 --> 00:01:50.835
Where did we come from?

00:01:50.835 --> 00:01:53.100
How did we get here?

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:55.100
And, where are we going?

00:01:56.808 --> 00:01:59.800
As you know, two of these
questions are tractable

00:01:59.800 --> 00:02:02.050
to scientific inquiry.

00:02:02.050 --> 00:02:04.666
And this is the question of anthropogeny,

00:02:04.666 --> 00:02:06.391
explaining the origin of humans,

00:02:06.391 --> 00:02:10.581
where did we come from
and how did we get here.

00:02:10.581 --> 00:02:13.598
And so pursuing this
discipline involves most

00:02:13.598 --> 00:02:15.020
academic disciplines.

00:02:15.020 --> 00:02:18.617
